# Download miniconda/ anaconda

## Miniconda
https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html

## Anaconda
https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual

# Install by following the instructions
https://docs.conda.io/projects/conda/en/latest/user-guide/install/macos.html

# Create a new conda environment 
conda create -n rna-seq

# Activate the environment
conda activate rna-seq

# Add new channels to the environment
conda config --add channels bioconda
conda config --add channels conda-forge

# Install SRA tools 
conda install sra-tools

# Find you favorite GEO dataset
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gds

# Locate the SRA entry at the bottom of the page e.g.
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE88830

# Preparation

## Check your current directory
pwd

## List files in your current directory
ls

## Change the current directory
cd {name_of_directory}
cd Documents

## Create folder for RNAseq datasets (e.g.)
mkdir RNAseq_datasets
cd RNAseq_datasets

## Create folder for your dataset (e.g.)
mkdir GSE88830

# Click on the SRA entry at the bottom of the page e.g.
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE88830

# Click on "Send results to Run selector"

# In the Select field download Metadata
## Option 1 - Total
## Option 2 - Select only relevant data

